reviews.review_text: Good Sound Good Sound, decent set list, and really doesn't matter who is on keyboards to review the show.

My First Oakland Show Damn good show. Living in Houston at the time, it was great to finally get out west. Caught the last two of the three-night "comback" shows after Garcia's 5 day "Jerry sleep" coma. Had a rip-roar'n good time.
sure as your born good sound,Grate Playin' Historical Run.thanx to all involved.Dig it

Looking for a gold ring down inside.. Good sound on this one..With a very interesting set list..love the Sugaree>Jack Straw to end the 1st set..and this carries over into 2nd set with the Box of Rain to open and Willie and the Hand Jive> Iko out of space..This is a solid well played show for 86' which was a limited year due to Jerry's illness..so please>GIVE IT A WHIRL>Forever Grateful>Forever Dead!!!!!!!!!!!!LIFER@!

have this on cassette got this from a friend whos friend i hear won a contest to tape at the sbd for this show i have it as 75%sbd and 25% ambient audience mix. sounds just like the tape i have so i assume it's from the same source no? love the stella blue! in 200 shows when jerry sang dust off those rusty strings just one more time,,was one of those one in a million dead moments you go to all those shows for!
Above Average 86 Highlights: Iko Iko (fast tempo)

Let the good times roll! How happy were we to have Jerry back?
My first set of shows after getting out of the Army. 
Couldn't have been happier the Dead were touring again.
love the "Hand Jive"
